f:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Drift is best suited for B2B sales teams, demand generation, enterprise marketing, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Forethought, meanwhile, shines for mid market support, SaaS companies, ticket heavy teams, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2015, Drift describes itself as \"Conversational AI platform for sales and customer engagement on websites.\" Forethought, established in 2018, positions itself as \"Generative AI platform for customer support automation and ticket intelligence.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
10:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Forethought** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (8 vs 6). However, this does not mean Drift is a poor choice — far from it. Drift excels in its own right, particularly for B2B sales teams and demand generation.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value strong ticket categorization and routing, go with Forethought. If excellent for b2b lead qualification matters more to you, Drift is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
